\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-002_Assemble_fine-surface_operators_with_geodesic_neighborhoods_tangent_frames_and_boundary_masks/stdout.jsonl:35:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_17\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command_execution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/bin/bash -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,220p' docs/pipeline_notes.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aggregated_output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"# Pipeline notes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Recommended workflow\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n1. Use FlyWire Codex bulk exports for stable metadata snapshots.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n2. Use CAVE / fafbseg for programmatic per-neuron access.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n3. Build local preprocessed assets so the simulator does not talk to FlyWire live during runtime.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Why this repo uses selective meshing\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe female whole brain is the structural scaffold, but the final simulation should only keep a small subset in a mesh-wave state at once. That matches a multiresolution strategy:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- whole brain mapped,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- selected circuit meshed,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- only active patches numerically updated.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Artifact contracts\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Subset-selection contract\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMilestone 4 subset generation writes one artifact bundle per named preset under\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`data/interim/subsets/<preset>/`:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `root_ids.txt`: simulator-facing root-id list\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `selected_neurons.csv`: filtered registry rows for the preset\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `subset_stats.json`: graph counts, role counts, and boundary summaries\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `subset_manifest.json`: resolved selection rules plus the selected neuron roster\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `preview.md`: lightweight Markdown/Mermaid preview for quick inspection\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe active preset also refreshes the path named by `config.paths.selected_root_ids`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nso downstream pipeline steps can switch subsets without code changes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Geometry handoff contract\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMilestone 5 uses the versioned geometry bundle contract\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`geometry_bundle.v1`. One canonical library path builder owns the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfilenames below, and both `scripts/02_fetch_meshes.py` plus\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py` use it directly.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nPer neuron, the bundle layout is:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.meshes_raw_dir/<root_id>.ply`: raw mesh\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.skeletons_raw_dir/<root_id>.swc`: raw skeleton\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_mesh_dir/<root_id>.ply`: simplified mesh\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_graph.npz`: surface graph\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_patch_graph.npz`: patch graph\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_descriptors.json`: derived descriptor sidecar\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_qa.json`: QA sidecar\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe processed graph archives intentionally separate fine and coarse data:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the surface graph stores the simplified mesh vertices/faces, sparse surface adjacency/Laplacian arrays, and `surface_to_patch` so every surface vertex has an explicit coarse patch assignment\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the patch graph stores sparse coarse adjacency/Laplacian arrays plus `patch_sizes`, `patch_centroids`, `patch_seed_vertices`, and CSR-style `member_vertex_indices` / `member_vertex_indptr` arrays for reconstructing patch membership deterministically\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the operator bundle contract now also reserves `fine_operator` and `coarse_operator` roles in the processed manifest; during migration those roles point to the same surface/patch graph archives instead of inventing a second filename scheme\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_transfer_operators.npz` stores explicit fine/coarse transfer structure and sparse restriction/prolongation matrices\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_operator_metadata.json` records the realized discretization family, fallback mode, boundary mode, geodesic-neighborhood settings, and transfer availability for downstream discovery\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`config.paths.manifest_json` records the bundle contract version, dataset,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nmaterialization version, meshing-config snapshot, and per-root asset\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nstatuses/paths. Raw fetch runs also record `raw_asset_provenance` per\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nroot ID so cache hits, refetches, skips, validation failures, and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\noptional skeleton fetch errors can be audited without reading console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nlogs. Processed bundle records also expose `artifact_sources` so each\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nsimplified mesh, surface graph, patch graph, and sidecar points back to\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nthe raw mesh and skeleton inputs it was built against.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nDescriptor and QA rationale:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `docs/geometry_descriptor_qa.md` documents the default `meshing.qa_thresholds`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  profile, what each descriptor bucket is meant to capture, and which failed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  checks should block downstream use by default.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nCompatibility shim:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_meta.json` is still written as\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  a legacy metadata pointer so older consumers can keep reading the prior\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  sidecar name during migration.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `docs/operator_bundle_design.md` is the authoritative Milestone 6 operator\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  decision note; later tickets should cite it instead of re-litigating the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  default discretization family.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"exit_code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-002_Assemble_fine-surface_operators_with_geodesic_neighborhoods_tangent_frames_and_boundary_masks/stdout.jsonl:40:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_19\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command_execution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/bin/bash -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/test_config_paths.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aggregated_output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"from __future__ import annotations\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport os\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport subprocess\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport sys\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport tempfile\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport textwrap\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport unittest\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nSRC = ROOT / \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"src\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nsys.path.insert(0, str(SRC))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom flywire_wave.config import get_config_path, get_project_root, load_config\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nclass ConfigPathResolutionTest(unittest.TestCase):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def test_load_config_resolves_paths_against_explicit_project_root(self) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmp_dir_str:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            tmp_dir = Path(tmp_dir_str)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            config_path = tmp_dir / \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"config.yaml\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            config_path.write_text(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                textwrap.dedent(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                    paths:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                      neuron_registry_csv: data/interim/registry/neuron_registry.csv\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                      subset_output_dir: data/interim/subsets\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                ).strip()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                + \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                encoding=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"utf-8\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            cfg = load_config(config_path, project_root=tmp_dir)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            self.assertEqual(get_config_path(cfg), config_path.resolve())\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            self.assertEqual(get_project_root(cfg), tmp_dir.resolve())\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            self.assertEqual(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                cfg[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"paths\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"][\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"neuron_registry_csv\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"],\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                str((tmp_dir / \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"data/interim/registry/neuron_registry.csv\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\").resolve()),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            self.assertEqual(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                cfg[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"paths\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"][\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"subset_output_dir\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"],\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                str((tmp_dir / \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"data/interim/subsets\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\").resolve()),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            self.assertEqual(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                cfg[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"paths\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"][\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"classification_csv\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"],\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                str((tmp_dir / \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"data/raw/codex/classification.csv\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\").resolve()),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nclass PipelineConfigPathIntegrationTest(unittest.TestCase):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def test_pipeline_scripts_work_from_non_repo_cwd_with_absolute_config_path(self) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory(dir=ROOT) as fixture_dir_str:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            fixture_dir = Path(fixture_dir_str)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            fixture_rel = fixture_dir.relative_to(ROOT)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as outside_dir_str:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                outside_dir = Path(outside_dir_str)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                config_path = _write_pipeline_fixture(fixture_dir, fixture_rel)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                stub_dir = _write_stub_dependencies(fixture_dir)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                env = os.environ.copy()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                env[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"FLYWIRE_TOKEN\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"] = \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                existing_pythonpath = env.get(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"PYTHONPATH\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\