\\\\n**Workload split:** Math/physics-heavy  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Suggested lead:** Grant  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Implementation support:** Jack\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Goal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nTurn neuron surfaces into simulation-ready numerical objects.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Build\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- adjacency structures  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- geodesic neighborhoods  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- graph or cotangent Laplacian  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- patch graph  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- local tangent frames  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- boundary masks  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- optional anisotropy tensors  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- fine-to-coarse transfer operators\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Agent implements:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- sparse matrix construction code  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- asset serialization  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- performance optimization  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- operator test harnesses  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- visualization of operator outputs on meshes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Agent researches and weighs options, chooses best, implements and documents all reasoning in a mark down file:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- choosing the correct discretization family  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- deciding whether to use graph-based or mesh-based operators  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- specifying stability-relevant properties  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- defining what should be conserved or damped  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- checking whether the operator is faithful enough to the intended physics\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Done when\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- a pulse can be initialized on a single neuron  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- propagation on the surface is numerically stable  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- coarse and fine operators can be compared  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- operator quality metrics exist\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Milestone 7 — Map synapses and define inter-neuron coupling\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Workload split:** Shared, leaning math/physics  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Suggested lead:** Shared\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"exit_code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-002_Assemble_fine-surface_operators_with_geodesic_neighborhoods_tangent_frames_and_boundary_masks/stdout.jsonl:47:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_23\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command_execution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/bin/bash -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '36,66p' agent_tickets/milestone_6_surface_discretization_tickets.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aggregated_output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"## FW-M6-002 - Assemble fine-surface operators with geodesic neighborhoods, tangent frames, and boundary masks\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Status: open\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Priority: high\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Source: Milestone 6 roadmap 2026-03-21\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Area: fine operators / mesh numerics / sparse assembly\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Problem\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe current processed surface graph is still a Milestone 5 scaffold. It exposes simplified mesh connectivity and a uniform graph Laplacian, but it does not yet provide the numerical objects Milestone 6 actually needs: geodesic neighborhoods, boundary masks, local tangent frames, metric-aware weights, or a surface operator whose supporting geometry is explicit enough to debug and validate. That leaves the repo unable to build a simulation-ready single-neuron surface state without rewriting the existing graph archive by hand.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Requested Change\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nImplement the fine-surface operator builder tha